  <context>
    <background>
      The structural fallback ladder was added in R3.1 / R4 era to handle nodes that didn't have ActionType
      populated — it inferred dispatch from node name patterns ("Start", "LoadKnowledge", "ReturnResponse").
      That heuristic was brittle and contributed to the R7 motivation. Post-task 024, the orchestrator reads
      dispatch directly; the ladder is unreachable code.
    </background>
