    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Delete call sites first">
      Remove every call to the four helpers from within `ExecuteNodeAsync` and any other method that invoked them. After this step, the helpers are unreferenced (Roslyn will warn).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Delete the four helpers">
      Remove the method bodies + their XML doc comments + any private fields they exclusively used.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Sweep adjacent dead code">
      If the deleted helpers had supporting types (e.g., helper records, internal enums) that are now unused, delete those too. Be conservative — only delete if grep confirms zero references.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Update tests">
      Find tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` that asserted the structural inference behavior. Per ADR-038 build-vs-maintain criteria: these are SCAFFOLDING (no behavior remains to assert) — DELETE. Run `/test-diet` mentally — these tests are not in any KEEP category.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build + test">
      `dotnet build` — 0 errors, 0 new warnings (any "unused" warnings indicate missed call sites).
      `dotnet test` — green.
